Sentencas: In this work, the effects of ethylene on the solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) anode were investigated both for an SOFC single cell and an SOFC stack.
Titulo: Effects of low hydrocarbons on the solid oxide fuel cell anode

Sentencas: Two fuels were used to observe the effects that low hydrocarbons (over C1-hydrocarbons) in the reformate gas stream have on the SOFC anode.
Titulo: Effects of low hydrocarbons on the solid oxide fuel cell anode

Sentencas: Methane or ethylene was supplied to the electrolyte-supported SOFC anode.
Titulo: Effects of low hydrocarbons on the solid oxide fuel cell anode

Sentencas: Using ethylene as a fuel, catastrophic degradation of SOFC performance was observed due to ethylene-induced carbon deposition onto the SOFC anode.
Titulo: Effects of low hydrocarbons on the solid oxide fuel cell anode

Sentencas: Thus, a new methodology, termed post-reforming, is introduced for the removal of low hydrocarbons (over C1-hydrocarbons) from the reformate gas stream.
Titulo: Effects of low hydrocarbons on the solid oxide fuel cell anode

Sentencas: The CGO-Ru catalyst was selected as the post-reforming catalyst because of its high selectivity for removing low hydrocarbons (over C1-hydrocarbons) and for its long-term stability.
Titulo: Effects of low hydrocarbons on the solid oxide fuel cell anode

Sentencas: The diesel reformer and post-reformer were continuously operated for similar to 250 h in coupled-operation mode.
Titulo: Effects of low hydrocarbons on the solid oxide fuel cell anode

Sentencas: The reforming performance was not degraded, and low hydrocarbons (over C1-hydrocarbons) in the diesel reformate were completely removed.
Titulo: Effects of low hydrocarbons on the solid oxide fuel cell anode
